          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does the Helpful Content System target AI-generated content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The system targets content that lacks genuine value for readers, regardless of how it was produced. AI-assisted content that has been fact-checked, edited by a human expert, and provides original perspectives is not targeted. Mass-produced, unreviewed, low-originality AI content is what the classifier is designed to demote.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I know if my site was hit by the Helpful Content System?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Unlike a Google Penalty, there is no Search Console notification. Look for gradual, sustained traffic declines in Google Search Console around documented update dates (August 2022, September 2023, March 2024). Helpful content impacts tend to be slow and cumulative rather than sudden drops overnight.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I recover from a Helpful Content System hit?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, but recovery is slow. Audit your site for thin content, unoriginal summaries, and keyword-targeted pages lacking genuine expertise. Improve, consolidate, or remove the weakest material. The system runs continuously and re-evaluates sites over time. Recovery typically spans weeks to months after improvement.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is the Helpful Content System different from a core update?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Core updates are broad quality reassessments run several times per year. The Helpful Content System is a specific, continuously running classifier focused on one question: is this content made for people or for search engines? In March 2024, Google folded the Helpful Content System into its core ranking systems.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

